---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Lucas Sommer" description="Lucas Sommer is a serial entrepreneur from Oregon. Founded 8+ companies across marketing, construction, wine, fintech, and AI. Two acquisitions. Featured in Forbes, NBC News, and Entrepreneur.com.">

  <article class="container">

    <div class="bio-hero">
      <h1>I've been building things since my dorm room.</h1>
      <p class="bio-lede">
        I'm Lucas Sommer — a serial entrepreneur from Newberg, Oregon. I build companies, write about the entrepreneurial mindset, and try to make useful things for people who are building too.
      </p>
      <p class="bio-lede">
        I live in Oregon with my wife Caitlin, our two boys — Cameron (9) and Ben (7) — and our dog Ace. They're the reason I build, and the reason I come home. Everything else is context.
      </p>
      <p class="bio-lede">
        I've started companies in music, marketing, luxury fashion, fintech, construction, agriculture, and AI. Some worked. Some didn't. All of them taught me something I couldn't have learned any other way.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Story -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>The Short Version</h2>
      <p>Valedictorian in a small Oregon town. Full academic scholarship to the University of Miami studying finance and music. Built four music companies from my dorm room. Won the Budgetball championship. First employee at The Launch Pad, where I consulted 400+ student businesses. Won WeMedia Pitch It! ($25K) for Audimated — featured on NBC News, Entrepreneur.com, and Forbes. Built Socialated from $1,000 to 13 employees before it was acquired. Formed Lucas Sommer Inc., merged it with my partner Bryan Lozano's company to create Ad-Apt — where we've delivered results for Netflix, Payless (400% ROAS), Teton Gravity Research (7.2x ROAS), Circle K, and Benchmade. Ran operations at Del Toro Shoes. Led marketing at LeadsRx (acquired by Unbounce) and guest lectured at Georgetown.</p>
      <p>Today I run <a href="/projects/ad-apt">Ad-Apt</a> (marketing agency serving Netflix, Circle K, Benchmade, Payless), <a href="/projects/boss-pdx">Boss PDX</a> (construction in Portland), <a href="/projects/grove-vineyard">Grove Vineyard</a> (Willamette Valley vineyard), and <a href="/projects/intraalpha">IntraAlpha</a> (algo trading). I'm building <a href="/projects/onit">Onit</a> — an AI-powered marketing platform — and writing a book called <a href="/projects/monkey-business">Monkey Business</a> about why your brain is wired to fail at entrepreneurship. LeadsRx, where I ran marketing, was acquired by Unbounce. Socialated, the agency I built from $1K, was acquired by Virsocom. Two companies I helped build got acquired. Now I'm building more.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Timeline -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>The Timeline</h2>
      <div class="timeline">

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">Newberg, Oregon</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Small-town kid, big ambitions</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Grew up in the Willamette Valley. Graduated valedictorian. Knew I wanted to build things — just didn't know what yet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2006 - 2010</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">University of Miami</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">BS Finance + Music (2006-2008), MBA Entrepreneurship (2008-2010)</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Full academic scholarship. Started a recording studio in my dorm room and built <strong>four music companies</strong>: 13flat recording studio, Originalheat.com, Breakrecords.net, and Breakrecords publishing. Won the Budgetball championship. Became the first employee at The Launch Pad — U of Miami's new entrepreneurship department — where I consulted 400+ student and alumni businesses.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">Feb 2009 - Jan 2015</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Audimated</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Founder & CEO</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Online marketplace for independent musicians and fans — 10,000+ artists at peak. Distribution to iTunes, Rhapsody, and eMusic. Fans could earn money promoting artists they loved. Won the <strong>WeMedia Pitch It! Contest</strong> ($25K grand prize). Featured on <strong>NBC News, Entrepreneur.com, Forbes</strong>. Had a Wikipedia page. Free signup, 10% transaction fee model.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2011 - 2014</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Socialated</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Founder</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Started in a spare bedroom with $1,000. Grew from social media marketing to a full-service agency with 13 employees servicing clients worldwide — SEO, social, customer service evaluations, and personalized marketing reports. Acquired by Virsocom Ventures in 2014.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">Feb 2014 - Feb 2015</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Virsocom Ventures</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Digital Marketing Director</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Post-acquisition role leading digital marketing strategy and operations after Socialated was acquired.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">Apr 2017 - Jan 2019</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Del Toro Shoes</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Partner</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Joined the luxury handmade Italian shoe brand in Miami. Helped secure a strategic investment and took on a full-time operational role.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">May 2019 - Apr 2021</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">LeadsRx</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Director of Marketing</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Led marketing for a marketing attribution SaaS platform serving 5,000+ global brands and agencies including iHeartMedia, Casper, and Rakuten. Published in MarketingProfs. Guest lectured at Georgetown University's McDonough School of Business. Hosted the Attribution Marketing Podcast. LeadsRx was later <strong>acquired by Unbounce</strong> (Crest Rock Partners portfolio) in January 2022.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2014</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Lucas Sommer Inc.</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Founder</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">After Virsocom acquired Socialated, I formed Lucas Sommer Inc. and have held it ever since. My Socialated partner Bryan Lozano formed Bryan Lozano Inc. We both continued building client bases independently — until we merged the two companies to create Ad-Apt.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2014 - Present</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Ad-Apt</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">CEO & Co-Founder (with Bryan Lozano)</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Merged Lucas Sommer Inc. and Bryan Lozano Inc. into a full-service digital marketing agency. Clients include <strong>Netflix, Circle K (Couche-Tard), Payless (400% ROAS, 1,200% e-commerce growth), Teton Gravity Research (7.2x ROAS), Benchmade Knives</strong>, 16 law firms, and hundreds more. Built the car wash relationship from Clean Freak through True Blue ($1M+ new sales, 500% subscription growth) to Couche-Tard's acquisition in 2023.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">Present</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Boss PDX + Grove Vineyard + IntraAlpha</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Founder</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Running a construction company in Portland, developing a Willamette Valley vineyard (Pinot Noir & Chardonnay), and operating an algo trading platform with Discord community.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2026</div>
          <div class="timeline-title">Onit + Monkey Business</div>
          <div class="timeline-role">Building</div>
          <p class="timeline-desc">Building an AI-powered marketing platform (Onit) that productizes 15 years of agency experience. Writing a book (Monkey Business) on the entrepreneurial mindset — 20 chapters on why your brain is wired for survival, not business.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- AI -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>My Thoughts on AI</h2>
      <p>Claude Desktop with its agentic components — scheduler, skills, dispatch — sits on top of your local machine with access to every open source tool, every API, every piece of hardware or cloud you can throw at it. Opus 4.6 is the greatest productive force on earth. The closed ecosystem (Anthropic/Claude) sitting on top of the open source local layer is godmode.</p>
      <p>This entire website — 9 pages, deep research from my LinkedIn, Notion, and the web, an interactive map, email capture, mobile-responsive design, real content pulled from my entire career — was built in a single Claude Code session. That's not a pitch. That's what happened.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>How I Think</h2>
      <div class="philosophy-grid">
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h3>Assets over income</h3>
          <p>Everything I do should trade time, expertise, and energy for scarce, rare assets. Infrastructure is an asset.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h3>Time is the scarcest resource</h3>
          <p>Tasks and goals should be organized by their ability to save my time or save others theirs. Time-saving infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h3>Execution is everything</h3>
          <p>Ideas are the easy part. Writing a business plan is not action. Planning is not doing. What are you going to do about it?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h3>Seek the margin</h3>
          <p>Don't find the hardest problem — find the biggest gap between what the market pays and what it costs you to deliver.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Press -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>Featured In</h2>
      <div class="press-grid">
        <span class="press-chip">Forbes</span>
        <span class="press-chip">NBC News</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Entrepreneur.com</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Reuters</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Georgetown University</span>
        <span class="press-chip">MarketingProfs</span>
        <span class="press-chip">StartupNation</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Prowly</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Career Karma</span>
        <span class="press-chip">Radio & TV Business Report</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Memberships -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>Awards, Memberships & Speaking</h2>
      <ul class="awards-list">
        <li><strong>WeMedia Pitch It! Contest</strong> — Grand prize winner ($25,000) for Audimated</li>
        <li><strong>University of Miami Budgetball Champion</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Young Entrepreneur Council (YEC)</strong> — Member</li>
        <li><strong>Georgetown University</strong> — Guest lecturer, McDonough School of Business</li>
        <li><strong>University of Miami</strong> — First employee at The Launch Pad entrepreneurship department; frequent guest lecturer on entrepreneurship</li>
        <li><strong>Operation Agency Freedom Podcast</strong> — Guest (Ep. 171: College, Culture Shock, and Entrepreneurship)</li>
        <li><strong>Attribution Marketing Podcast</strong> — Host</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Connect -->
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>Connect</h2>
      <p>I'm most active on <a href="https://twitter.com/lucasbsommer" target="_blank">Twitter/X</a>. You can also find me on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/lucasbsommer" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> and <a href="https://github.com/lucasbsommer" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Email Capture -->
    <div class="email-capture" style="margin-bottom:4rem;">
      <h3>Follow the journey</h3>
      <p class="capture-sub">I build in public across marketing, construction, wine, trading, and AI. Get updates when I ship something, learn something, or write something worth reading.</p>
      <form class="email-form" onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); this.querySelector('button').textContent='Subscribed!'; this.querySelector('button').disabled=true;">
        <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Bio hero */
  .bio-hero {
    padding: 4rem 0 0;
  }

  .bio-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .bio-lede {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .bio-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .bio-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bio-section p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .bio-section p + p {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 7px;
    top: 4px;
    bottom: 4px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline-item:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: -2.5rem;
    top: 4px;
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 2.5px solid var(--border);
    z-index: 1;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .timeline-item.highlight .timeline-dot {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-soft);
  }

  .timeline-year {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .timeline-title {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .timeline-role {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .timeline-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .timeline-desc strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Philosophy cards */
  .philosophy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .philosophy-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .philosophy-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .philosophy-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Press chips */
  .press-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .press-chip {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  /* Awards list */
  .awards-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .awards-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .awards-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.65em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .awards-list li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Email Capture */
  .email-capture {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .email-capture h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .email-capture .capture-sub {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .email-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .email-form input[type="email"] {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.85rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background: var(--bg);
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .email-form input[type="email"]:focus {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .email-form input[type="email"]::placeholder {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .email-form button {
    padding: 0.55rem 1.15rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #ffffff;
    border: none;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .email-form button:hover {
    background: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .bio-hero { padding-top: 3rem; }
    .bio-hero h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .bio-lede { font-size: 1rem; }
    .philosophy-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .email-form { flex-direction: column; }
    .email-form button { width: 100%; padding: 0.65rem 1rem; }
  }
</style>
